	<config>
		<documentation file="www/documentation.rtf"> 
RELAY TIMER

This driver enables timed control of a device controlled by a relay. It is an alternative to the relay driver included by default in My Drivers.

Each press of the icon cycles through the list of duration options. Set the duration options as comma-delimited minutes in the driver’s "Countdown Times" property.

To turn the system off, either continue to cycle through the options until Off is shown, or wait 5 seconds from the last option selected and the next press of the icon will turn the timer off.

Events fire when the timer reaches each of the timed countdowns. You can use these with custom programming as required.

You can also connect the driver to a relay or associate it with a switched light. The relay connection can be found on the connections tab.  To associate with a light switch select Light Switch as the control method.  Then select the light switch which is used to control the device.

The "User timer if turned on manually" property enables you to set a timer automatically if the device is turned on via the relay or light switch.  Set this property to "Yes" then select the required run time from the dropdown box below.

In each room where you want the timer to appear select the room and page in Composer and add make the timer visible.

A keypad button link connection is available which also cycles through the time choices. The LED will indicate if the button has been pressed to select the next time ("Pressed LED Color"), if the timer is running ("On LED Color"), or if the device is off ("Off LED Color"). Colors can be customized for each of these states.

CHANGES IN VERSION 35: Fixed Defect #40015 - Experience driver repopulates all default timers under system design on controller reboot or project reload.

CHANGES IN VERSION 36: Fixed Defect #2694 / #2106 - Timer - Experience Driver not initializing properly

CHANGES IN VERSION 38: Updated icons.

</documentation>
